---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Access to Doctorate | Brenkley Doctoral College" description="Brenkley Doctoral College's Access to Doctorate programme — a one-year foundation pathway for professionals preparing for doctoral-level study. £2,800 total.">

  <section class="bg-surface border-b border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-4">Programme</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Access to Doctorate</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-accent font-medium mb-4">Foundation Pathway &mdash; One Year &mdash; £2,800 total</p>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-2xl">The Access to Doctorate programme is a structured, one-year preparatory pathway for professionals who are interested in doctoral study but want to build their academic confidence, research skills, and proposal quality before applying to a full programme.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-12">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">1 Year</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Part-time, designed to fit around a professional schedule</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">£2,800</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Total fee. Two instalments available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent mb-2">Pathway to PhD</div>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted">Successful completion may lead to entry exemptions on Brenkley Doctoral College doctoral programmes</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">Who It's For</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Building Your Foundation</h2>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">The Access to Doctorate programme is for professionals who know they want to pursue doctoral study but are aware of specific gaps in their academic preparation. Perhaps you completed your undergraduate degree many years ago and want to refresh your academic writing and critical thinking. Perhaps you have no postgraduate qualification and want to demonstrate research capability before applying to a DBA or EdD. Perhaps you have a research idea but it is not yet clearly formulated.</p>
          <p class="text-muted mb-4">This programme bridges that gap. It is not a lesser substitute for doctoral study — it is a deliberate investment in your preparedness for it.</p>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-2 list-disc list-inside mt-4">
            <li>Professionals without a recent Master's degree</li>
            <li>Candidates wanting to test doctoral readiness before committing</li>
            <li>Professionals whose research idea needs development</li>
            <li>Career changers moving into a new research domain</li>
            <li>Professionals returning to academic study after a long break</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="section-label mb-3">What You Will Develop</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Outcomes</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Academic Reading and Critical Thinking</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Systematic approaches to reading academic literature, evaluating evidence quality, and developing critical analytical skills appropriate for doctoral-level scholarship.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Academic Writing</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">The conventions of academic writing — argumentation, referencing, structure, and the discipline of clear scholarly prose. Practice assignments with detailed feedback.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Research Thinking</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">Introduction to research paradigms, basic research design, and the difference between research questions and management problems. Foundation for formal methods training in a doctoral programme.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="card">
              <h3 class="font-semibold mb-1">Doctoral Research Proposal</h3>
              <p class="text-muted text-sm">A completed, supervisor-reviewed draft doctoral research proposal, ready for submission as part of a formal doctoral application.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Programme Content -->
  <section class="bg-surface border-y border-border py-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <p class="section-label mb-3">Programme Content</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What You Will Cover</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Term 1: Foundations of Scholarly Inquiry</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Introduction to academic reading and critical analysis</li>
            <li>Academic writing: conventions and practice</li>
            <li>What is a research question?</li>
            <li>Overview of research paradigms</li>
            <li>Foundations of literature searching and management</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Term 2: Developing Your Research Idea</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Identifying and refining a research question</li>
            <li>Introduction to qualitative and quantitative approaches</li>
            <li>Research ethics overview</li>
            <li>Practitioner-research positionality</li>
            <li>Writing the doctoral research proposal</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Term 3: Proposal Refinement and Application Preparation</h3>
          <ul class="text-muted text-sm space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
            <li>Proposal workshop — peer review and feedback</li>
            <li>Proposal finalisation with academic mentor feedback</li>
            <li>Doctoral application guidance</li>
            <li>Interview preparation</li>
            <li>Programme completion and certificate</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Academic Mentoring</h3>
          <p class="text-muted text-sm">Throughout the programme, you have access to an academic mentor — a Brenkley Doctoral College faculty member who provides guidance on your research idea and academic writing. Three formal mentor meetings are included, with email support between sessions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-6 text-center">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Begin your doctoral journey</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-8">The Access to Doctorate programme is the right first step if you are not quite ready for a full doctorate but know that is where you are heading. Invest one year in building your foundation — and enter your doctoral programme with confidence.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-4 justify-center flex-wrap">
        <a href="/apply" class="btn-primary">Enquire now</a>
        <a href="/connect" class="btn-outline">Speak to us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
